                <td width="436" class="texte"> 
                  <table width="450" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0">
                  <tr><td><span class="text-titre">Kalisto</td></tr>
                  <tr><td class="texte"><img src="../getimage.php?get=image&b=menureferences&r=6" align="right">In the words of Nicolas Gaume, President of Kalisto, "Our philosophy consists in being as thorough as possible, and therefore in using different platforms. We have always been particularly drawn to mobile platforms, but up until now, were somewhat unsure of their actual technological capacities. Today, thanks to its ExEn® technology, In-Fusio has totally sold us on the concept."</td></tr>
                  </table>
<BR>
                  <table width="450" border="0" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0">
                  <tr><td><span class="text-titre">Cryo Networks</td></tr>
                  <tr><td class="texte"><img src="../getimage.php?get=image&b=menureferences&r=7" align="right">"As a leader in the creation of virtual worlds on the Internet and a leading publisher of online games in Europe, Cryonetworks currently develops games for PC and Mac platforms. Due to the rapid development of entertainment products on mobile devices, we were also interested in developing our games on these new platforms," explains Patrice Rullier, C.E.O. of Cryonetworks. "Thanks to In-Fusio¹s well-established distribution network and their mastering of different mobile game technologies, we can now move our products into the growing mobile market."</td></tr>
